name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: Happy introduction birthday to the Voting Rights Act which was first introduced to Congress on March 17th, 1965. Let's celebrate by tweeting our representatives to let them know we want it to be reauthorized! @AlexPadilla4CA I know you're with us!

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: A new study from the Kaiser Family Foundation finds that 84% of Americans are concerned with voting rights. Voting rights are more of a concern than health care costs or immigration. Every voter should feel confident that their vote is valued & counted!  https://t.co/iKjKORtp8p

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: As abortion rights come under renewed threats, I'm happy to be endorsed by @PPActionCA for my defense of a woman's right to bodily autonomy. Thank you @PPActionCA!

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: Changes in voting rules are about voter suppression, not election protection. We’ve seen the restriction of rights not based on merit or danger, but instead for political theater and political gain. This is very dangerous and the threats to losing our democracy are tangible.

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: Election workers should feel safe doing their jobs, period. These workers are deserving of the public's trust and the government's protection.  https://t.co/KqffbiqknH

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: The most powerful thing we can do is vote. I spoke with @RandiRichTV of NBC about the importance of voting and the role of Black women in defending voting rights. Watch here:  https://t.co/k1bTntNXro

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: Happy International Women's Day!

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: As your SoS I'll protect our election integrity and expand transparency. I'll strengthen the reforms that led to record voter turnout, and I will solidify California’s reputation as a national leader on expanding voting rights. I won't back down and I won't let you down.

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: Just filed my paperwork to continue serving as your secretary of state! I've spent my career expanding access to the ballot to every eligible Californian. I hope to earn your vote in June and November!  https://t.co/0ZtQemS1XA

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: In Texas' first election since SB 1 passed, over 30% of mail in ballots were rejected in Harris County. These rules only serve to make voting more difficult, especially in communities with limited access to the polls.  https://t.co/c4OUUNfV15

name: Shirley Weber, PhD

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: This fall, voters will have a clear opportunity to reject candidates who run on a platform of party over country. They can hold accountable those seeking to use their platforms to erode confidence in our election system.

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: @POTUS said it perfectly last night

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: Why do I advocate for voting? My parents serve as my example. They were so committed to the right to vote that they offered our family home as a polling place. Every election, my father would move the furniture out of the house so our community had a place to vote.

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: As part of #BlackHistoryMonth @ElectBlackWomxn and @WomenCount have teamed up to highlight 23 Black women running to make big differences in public office. Please help us amplify our message with your support. Money is a megaphone!  https://t.co/hG7DryPLxh

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: Congratulations to Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson on her historic nomination to SCOTUS! Judge Jackson is a highly qualified jurist and former public defender who has devoted her career to advancing justice for every community. I look forward to her confirmation!

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: With their inaction, Congressional leaders are prioritizing states' rights over voting rights, allowing states to change the nature of voting & for state legislatures to overrule certified election results outright. Congress must step in as Americans prepare to vote this year.

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: States aren't passing restrictive voting rights because they think there’s fraud. They know that there’s no fraud. That’s not the issue. The issue is that you are showing up, that you are standing in line. That you are asking to be heard and have your vote counted.

name: Shirley Weber, PhD
tweet: NEW: Read my op-ed with Michigan Secretary of State @JocelynBenson. In states from coast to coast, the Big Lie is on the ballot, and our democracy simply cannot afford for any of us to sit out this fight.  https://t.co/c3aIHdgKDl
